replies.body:
You need some serious thinking if you think the way you talk to people is okay.. it's not, I know because I got chat / ranked restricted about 8 times in row, and I did the same thing you did. I raged at Riot, blamed them for accusing me without reason. It was hard admitting that I had been a total jackass, and that my behaviour was terrible. 

Soon I realised I don't want to be banned or permanently muted or anything, so I changed the way I communicate in game by changing all those "wtf", "are you retarded?" and "omg noob??" kind of things into "np" and "xD" type of messages. Since that I haven't had any trouble, which essentially means that the punishment system works, and can improve player's behaviour permanently. I actually enjoy more being positive, even if someone flames at me. I reply with positivity, and most of the time it might even transform their behaviour aswell. Too bad though, permabans are quite harsh .. I don't understand why they are given so "easily" these days :(

{{champion:44}}
